The function h(x) is continuous on (0, ), decreasing since the derivative \( h'(x) = -2 \sin x \), which is negative in (0, ) because sin x is positive there. Therefore, h(x) is strictly decreasing from 1 to -3 over (0, ). Therefore, the equation \( a = h(x) \) has exactly one solution in (0, ) for each a in (-3, 1), and no solutions otherwise.
